Angel Salcedo joined WCVB Channel 5 as a sports reporter and producer for SportsCenter 5 in June 2023. As part of WCVB’s award-winning sports team, Angel works alongside lead sports anchor Duke Castiglione and sports reporters Josh Brogadir and Naoko Funayama. While at KOAT, Angel covered a variety of breaking news, political and sports stories. In his role as sports reporter and fill-in sports anchor, Angel reported from the sidelines for KOAT’s “The Rundown” football show and reported live from the University of New Mexico football games. He also provided live reports from the Dell Technologies Championship PGA golf event, as well as local color commentary when reporting live from the 2018 Boston Red Sox Championship Parade. Angel joined KOAT upon graduating from Emerson College in Boston with a degree in Broadcast Journalism. He was the News Director of the school’s news station, WEBN News, and the host of Good Morning Emerson for three years. Fluent in English and Spanish, Angel is skilled at bilingual story gathering and has directed, produced, and written for WEBN’s weekly Spanish newscast. When he’s not reporting, chances are you can find Angel on the golf course. He developed a love for the game of golf just over five years ago and has since become a scratch player. Hearst Television participates in various affiliate marketing programs, which means we may get paid commissions on editorially chosen products purchased through our links to retailer sites.'}]
